        "created_at": "2017-11-27T12:57:08.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I bought a bunch of these without tasting in 375 to have some nice bdx to drink on nights when SWMBO is not joining me.  I opened the first bottle last night.  It was . . . a surprise.</p>\n<p>It was, in fact, a grenache.  I am not sure how grenache got in this bdx bottle, and I am not sure why anyone would want to do such a thing, but someone apparently decided to leave out the cab franc and to substitute some rhone ranger oversupply.</p>\n<p>It wasn\u2019t bad, exactly, but it also wasn\u2019t Pessac-L\u00e9ognan, at least to my palate, flawed though that palate may be.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
